# WordPress Performance and Queries

- Avoid heavy work in templates; precompute data in dedicated functions.
- Prevent N+1 patterns in loops; fetch data in batches where possible.
- Use `WP_Query` arguments carefully and reset post data with `wp_reset_postdata()`.
- Prefer object cache and transients for expensive operations.
- Avoid remote requests during page render unless strictly required.
- Load assets only where needed using conditional enqueue logic.
- Defer or async non-critical scripts where compatible with dependencies.
- Minimize autoloaded options and avoid large serialized option payloads.
